.TH locale 1
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Llocale\*O \- Displays information about locales
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*Llocale\*O
\*O[\*L\(hya\*O\ |\ \*L\(hym\*O]
.PP
.\" .zA "review, R1.1.2, XPG4"
\*Llocale\*O
\*O[\*L\(hyc\*O]
\*O[\*L\(hyk\*O]
\*Vname\*O\ \&.\&.\&.
.\" .zZ "review, R1.1.2, XPG4"
.sE
.PP
The \*Llocale\*O command writes information about the current locale
or all public locales.
.SH FLAGS
.PP
.VL 4m
.\" .zA "review, R1.1.2, XPG4"
.LI "\*L-a\*O"
Writes information about all available public locales.
.\" .zZ "review, R1.1.2, XPG4"
.LI "\*L-c\*O"
Writes the names of the specified locale categories.
.LI "\*L-k\*O"
Writes the names and values of specified locale keywords.
.LI "\*L-m\*O"
Writes the names of all available character map files.
.\" .LI "\*Vname\*O"
.\" Specifies a locale category or locale keyword.
.LE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "locale command"
.iX "locales, current and public"
.iX "displaying" "locale information"
The \*Llocale\*O command without any flags or arguments
writes to standard output the names and values of all the current locale
environment variables, such as \*LLANG\*O and \*LLC_COLLATE\*O.
.PP
The \*Llocale\*O command with
\*L-a\*O or \*L-m\*O flags displays information about available
locales and character maps on your system.  The \*Vname\*O
argument specifies a locale category or locale keyword.
.ML
.LI
If the \*L-a\*O flag is specified, \*Llocale\*O writes
the names of all available public locales.
These are locales that are available to any application.
.LI
If the \*L-m\*O flag is specified, \*Llocale\*O writes a list of the names of
all available character-mapping files. These values are suitable
variable values for the \*L-f\*O flag with the \*Llocaledef\*O command.
.LE
.PP
The \*Llocale\*O command with
the \*Vname\*O argument displays information about locale categories
and keywords in the current locale. For example, the command could display
information about the \*Ldecimal_point\*O keyword in the
\*LLC_NUMERIC\*O category or information about all keywords in the
\*LLC_NUMERIC\*O category. The \*Vname\*O parameter can be either a
locale category or a keyword from a category.
.PP
The \*L-c\*O and \*L-k\*O flags determine the information displayed by
the \*Llocale\*O command about the locale keywords:
.VL 11m
.LI "Flags Set"
Information Written to Standard Output
.LI "None"
Value of keyword specified by \*Vname\*O parameter or values of all
keywords in the category specified by \*Vname\*O parameter.
.LI "\*L-c\*O"
Name of category containing
the keyword specified by the \*Vname\*O
parameter or the name of the category specified by the \*Vname\*O
parameter, followed by values of locale keywords.
.LI "\*L-k\*O"
Names and values of locale keywords.
.LI "\*L-ck\*O"
Name of category, followed by names and values of locale keywords.
.LE
